However, jsonOrder processed in `processJsonOrder` should be processed one by one. Maybe by a queue, or there is a nice solution in Spring to do so. The idea is that jsonOrders are waiting when an order is executed within `processJsonOrder`. Currently, when two order updated arrive within seconds, order will be inserted into the database by `processJsonOrder` twice, as the thread processing the `jsonOrder` has not reached the commit point yet. There is some code in the `orderService` to check for duplicates on database level, but that doesn&#39;t help always.


