To draw skewed corners programmatically, you can create a custom view that extends View or one of its subclasses, such as RelativeLayout or FrameLayout. In the onDraw method of your custom view, you can use a Path object to define the shape of your view and then fill it with a color or a drawable.

Here&#39;s an example of how you can create a custom view with skewed corners

    class SkewedCornerView(context: Context, attrs: AttributeSet?) : View(context, attrs) {

    private val path = Path()

    override fun onDraw(canvas: Canvas?) {
        super.onDraw(canvas)
        canvas?.apply {
            path.reset()
            val cornerSize = resources.getDimensionPixelSize(R.dimen.corner_size).toFloat()
            val width = width.toFloat()
            val height = height.toFloat()
            path.moveTo(0f, 0f)
            path.lineTo(0f, height - cornerSize)
            path.lineTo(cornerSize, height)
            path.lineTo(width, height)
            path.lineTo(width, 0f)
